item.title: North Korea to increase number of nuclear weapons, says Kim Jong Un
item.description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un has committed to enhancing the nation's nuclear force and expanding its arsenal, as per state media reports. This follows the introduction of a new platform for more powerful intercontinental ballistic missiles. Kim highlighted that regional military alliances developing nuclear capabilities pose a grave threat, pushing North Korea to fortify its military strength.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Typhoon Yagi's wrath: Vietnam's Phong Chau bridge crumbles into Red River, collapse caught on camera
item.description: The collapse of Phong Chau Bridge in northern Vietnam due to Super Typhoon Yagi has resulted in significant casualties and ongoing rescue efforts. Over 60 lives have been lost, and authorities are searching for 13 missing individuals as the military constructs a temporary bridge. The landslides had killed at least 44 people.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: How did 358 migrants end up using same California address for US entry
item.description: An independent report from the Department of Homeland Security’s Office of the Inspector General found that more than 350 immigrants listed a single California address as their final destination using the CBP One app. The report highlights security vulnerabilities in the app, which has processed over 765,000 appointments since its launch.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Harris vs Trump: What to expect, when and where to watch key US presidential debate
item.description: The United States is gearing up for a second general election debate between Kamala Harris and Donald Trump after President Joe Biden withdrew from the race, endorsing Harris. Scheduled for September 11 at Philadelphia's National Constitution Center, the debate will be moderated by ABC News with specific rules on microphone usage and questioning.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: White Stripes sues Trump over use of iconic song 'Seven Nation Army' in campaign video: 'This machine sues fascists'
item.description: The White Stripes have initiated legal action against former US President Donald Trump for unauthorized use of their hit song 'Seven Nation Army' in a campaign video. The band alleges that neither Trump nor his campaign sought permission to use the song, which was featured in a social media post of Trump boarding a plane.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Who was James Earl Jones? 5 key facts about the man behind iconic Darth Vader voice and trailblazing actor
item.description: James Earl Jones, famed for his distinctive voice and powerful acting, died at 93. He voiced Darth Vader in Star Wars, followed his father's acting path, became the first Black actor to portray a U.S. president in film history, and delved into primal therapy.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US elections 2024: Harris leads national polls ahead of key debate, but Trump narrows gap in swing states
item.description: The 2024 US presidential election sees Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Donald Trump in a close race. Polls indicate Harris leads slightly, but swing states are crucial. The upcoming debate is expected to be pivotal, with both candidates vying for voter support in this high-stakes contest.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Biden will be watching Kamala Harris-Donald Trump debate in New York: 'He's incredibly proud'
item.description: The NYT polls which shows Trump is ahead of Kamala Harris by one percentage point came as a major upset for the Kamala Harris campaign just ahead of the debate on the ABC News. “As vice-president Harris has said since day one, we are the underdogs in this race. We have a lot of work to do to make sure we win this November, and that will require us to continue aggressively raising money," Kamala campaign said after the poll.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: New US antitrust trial focuses on Google's online ad dominance
item.description: Google is facing another antitrust lawsuit regarding its advertising technology. The justice department and several states argue that Google maintains a monopoly over online ad tech. This comes after recent court decisions declaring Google's search engine and Android app store as monopolies.

item.title: International hunt for man who poured hot coffee on Australian baby
item.description: Australian police have initiated an international search for a man accused of pouring hot coffee on a nine-month-old baby, resulting in serious burns. The suspect fled the country days after the incident in Brisbane. Authorities are determined to capture him and ensure he faces justice for intending to cause grave bodily harm.

item.title: Tuesday face-off: Kamala bunkers down to prep; Trump on rally spree
item.description: Kamala Harris and Donald Trump are preparing for Tuesday's presidential debate using different strategies. Harris is refining her responses in Pittsburgh, while Trump continues with campaign events without studying. The debate will highlight their differing approaches and visions for the country, along with underlying gender dynamics.

item.title: Trump claims Mark Zuckerberg told him 'I can't vote for a Democrat'; Meta denies
item.description: Trump said Mark Zuckerberg called him after the attempt on his life in Pennsylvania and said 'there’s no way I can vote for a Democrat in this election'. Zuckerberg said, as Trump claimed, he never supported a Republican before but this year will be different. Meta denied the claim and said Mark Zuckerberg maintains his announced position that he is not endorsing any candidate this election.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala Harris talks about debating Trump in her 2nd interview: No floor of how low he would go
item.description: Kamala Harris said in the upcoming ABC News debate, the first face-off between Kamala Harris and Donald Trump, she expects Trump to lie. ​"I mean, he plays with this really old and tired playbook, right? Where he, there’s no floor for him in terms of how low he would go. And we should be prepared for that," Kamala Harris said in her interview with Rickey Smiley.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: JD Vance speaks up for cats. Turns out it was for a 'conspiracy theory'
item.description: JD Vance made an X post based on reports that pet cats and ducks were getting stolen by Haitian immigrants in Ohio but police said there were no such reports. Last time JD Vance had something to do with cats, it was his infamous 'childless cat ladies' comment that he targeted at the Democrat politicians.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Black powder': How female genitalia is mutilated for 'magic', 'love potions' in this African nation
item.description: In Ivory Coast, witch doctors use potions made from the clitoris of girls subjected to female genital mutilation (FGM) for power and influence. The clitorises are dried, ground into powder, and sold or traded. FGM is condemned by Unicef as a severe violation of girls' rights and a dangerous act.
item.dc:creator: TOI News Desk

item.title: Haitian immigrants eating pet cats and ducks of residents in Ohio? Here's what happened
item.description: A day before the much-awaited debate between Donald Trump and Kamala Harris on ABC News, Republicans were up in arms on X claiming that Kamala Harris is responsible for illegal Haitian immigrants ravaging Ohio's Springfield. They latched on to a report of an Ohio woman arrested for killing and eating a cat -- in August.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Height of pettiness: Small-minded Trump seeks advantage from his large frame
item.description: Donald Trump insists on no artificial lifts for Kamala Harris in the upcoming presidential debate to ensure authenticity. Standing at six foot three inches, Trump towers over five foot four inch Harris. Despite no request from Harris's team, Trump's demand has drawn social media ridicule and criticism from her supporters.
item.dc:creator: Chidanand Rajghatta

item.title: Watch: Comedian heckles Nancy Pelosi, asks which stocks to buy
item.description: Nancy Pelosi was unperturbed as a comedian approached her at a book signing event posing as a Democrat supporters and then ranted against Donald Trump before asking her advice on which stocks to buy. The comedian called Nancy Pelosi the greatest options traders of all times when he was restrained by Nancy's security details and was shows the door.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala Harris launches policy page 'New Way Forward' ahead of Trump debate: Here’s what it says
item.description: ​​The detailed agenda, developed in collaboration with Minnesota Governor Tim Walz, lays out a vision for building a fairer economy, protecting civil rights, and addressing pressing national concerns like healthcare, climate change, and gun violence. Harris' proposals contrast sharply with former President Donald Trump’s "Project 2025" agenda, offering voters a stark choice on the direction of the nation.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Tulsi Gabbard says Dick Cheney has made it easier: 'A vote for Kamala Harris is...'
item.description: Tulsi Gabbard who joined Team Trump ahead of the election said she served in the Middle East and she believes that Bush's VP Dick Cheney is responsible for everything wrong in the Middle East. If Dick Cheney endorses Kamala Harris, then a vote for Kamala Harris would mean a vote for Dick Cheney and warmongers, Tulsi Gabbard said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
